# Stop Agent-Started Servers

When the agent starts a local server, dev server, watcher, preview, or other long-running process, it must stop that process before finishing the task unless the user explicitly asks to keep it running.

- Track which server commands were started by the agent during the task.
- Before the final response, stop those agent-started processes and confirm they are no longer listening on their ports when practical.
- Do not stop processes that were already running before the agent's work unless the user explicitly asks to stop them.
